ğŸ† Main Challenge: Compute Factorial

// Input: n
let n = 5;

// Step 1: Create a variable to store result
let factorial = 1;

// Step 2: Multiply numbers from 1 to n
for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
  factorial = factorial * i;
}

// Step 3: Print the result
console.log(factorial); // Output: 120 (5! = 5 Ã— 4 Ã— 3 Ã— 2 Ã— 1)

ğŸ‘‰ Kid-style explanation:
Imagine you are stacking chairs ğŸª‘.
On Day 1 â†’ 1 chair, Day 2 â†’ 2 chairs on top, Day 3 â†’ 3 chairs, â€¦ until Day N.
At the end â†’ you see how many different ways you can stack them â†’ thatâ€™s factorial! ğŸ‰


